name: Morning View Coffee Company

comment: It is handicap accessible if you can get the wheelchair through the narrow walk way.

name: Orlando Science Center
directions: On every public floor of the OSC, next to the doors of the typical gendered restroom stall is a single stall clearly marked as a gender-neutral restroom. The restrooms are located across from the big glass elevator on every floor.
comment: If you go in through the subway entrance, you can use their bathrooms without paying for admission.

name: Keller Auditorium
directions: On the first balcony (two flights up) when you walk out of the Auditorium it's on the left. Just keep walking and vear a little to the left. There are signs.
comment: This only works if you're seeing something at the Keller.

name: Veggie Galaxy vegan & vegetarian diner
directions:
Bathrooms are straight back in the hallway. There are signs inside and outside of both bathrooms that say "Please use the bathroom that best firs your gender identity."
Men's bathroom has one stall and a urinal. Women's bathroom has 2 stalls.

name: Veggie Galaxy - vegan & vegetarian diner
directions:
Restrooms are straight back in a hallway. Sign posted inside and outside of both restrooms reads "Please use the restroom that best fits your gender identity. If you experience any sort of harrassment in our restrooms, please inform our staff."
Men's has a large stall and urinal. Women's restroom has 2 stalls.

name: Cobham services
directions: First floor, follow the signs when you walk inside, should be at the back on the right.
comment: Can be used regardless of using any other services, safe to use if you don’t pass 100% of the time, but it’s always recommended that you use the restroom assigned to the gender that you feel comfortable to pass as, for your own safety, and for the sake of anyone that may happen to be in the restrooms at the time, as someone male-passing (identifying as male, and passing, even if not 100%) in the woman’s bathroom, may make someone uncomfortable.
